<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="281" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1158,1790]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1189,1214]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished among species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Odontorhagus" authorityName="Odontorhagus" box="[653,974,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Schizoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[653,785,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">Schizoptera</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[804,965,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">Odontorhagus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the relatively small body size, ovoid body shape, the distinctly curving M2 vein, the small process of the posterior margin of stVI, and the blade-like process of the subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
