<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1158,1790]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1369,1394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">Re-description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[396,453,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">Male</emphasis>
: length: 
<quantity box="[567,677,1369,1394]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="26" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
; body ovoid. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[851,1053,1369,1394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">COLORATION:</emphasis>
general coloration light brown; fuscous patch absent; Sc+C concolorous with remainder of hemelytra (
<figureCitation box="[942,1011,1405,1430]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,729,751]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,707]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,267,707]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Images of select type specimens that were either slide mounted or damaged, with an additional S. stricklandi specimen placed next to the damaged type for comparison." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164753/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1031,1406,1405,1430]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">SURFACE AND VESTITURE:</emphasis>
as in subgeneric description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[446,628,1441,1466]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">STRUCTURE:</emphasis>
<collectionCode box="[635,717,1442,1466]" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">HEAD</collectionCode>
: slightly rounded in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1161,1441,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,729,751]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,707]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,267,707]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Images of select type specimens that were either slide mounted or damaged, with an additional S. stricklandi specimen placed next to the damaged type for comparison." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164753/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="281">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); eyes about 2/3 as wide as synthlipsis. THORAX: as in subgeneric description; hemelytron as in subgeneric description; M2 vein distinctly curving anteriorly toward wing margin; anterior membranal cell wedge-shaped. ABDOMEN: as in subgeneric description; stVI with a small rounded process on posterior margin; subgenital plate distinctly asymmetrical; process of subgenital elongate and blade-shaped.
</paragraph>
